    "title": "See Both Sides",
    "description": "&quot;Well I ain't often right but I've never been wrong, \nSeldom turns out the way it does in the song. \nOnce in a while you get shown the light \nIn the strangest of places if you look at it right.&quot;\n– &quot;Scarlet Begonias&quot;, Grateful Dead, lyrics by Robert Hunter, &quot;From the Mars Hotel&quot; (1974)\n\n&quot;Yes, from the mountain of eternity we shall look down, and behold the whole plain spread before us. Down here we get lost and confused in the devious valleys that run off from the hills everywhere, and we cannot make out where the streams are going, and what there is behind that low shoulder of the hill yonder. But when we get to the summit peak and look down, it will all shape itself into one consistent whole, and we shall see it all at once.&quot;\n– Thomas Boston\n\n&quot;Praise be to the Lord my Rock,\n    who trains my hands for war,\n    my fingers for battle.&quot;\n– Psalm 144:1. \n",
